    "Lan et al. [32] proposed a unified learning paradigm to learn by modality the target representation, reliability, and classifier, collaboratively.",
    "Similar methods are also applied in the RGB-D tracking task.",
    "Ma and Xiang [54] constructed an augmented dictionary consisting of target and occlusion templates, thereby achieving accurate tracking even in the presence of heavy occlusion.",
    "SL-based trackers achieve promising results at the expense of computation cost.",
    "These trackers cannot meet the requirements of real-time tracking.Mean shift (MS)."
